sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Dashboard
    participant K8S as Kubernetes API
    participant Webhook as ODH Notebook Webhook
    participant ODH as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant DSPA as Data Science Pipelines API
    participant NB_Ctrl as Notebook Controller
    participant Culler as Notebook Culler
    participant Pod as Notebook Pod
    participant Router as OpenShift Router/Istio
    participant OAuth as OAuth Server

    Note over User,ODH: Flow 1: Notebook Creation and Provisioning
    User->>K8S: Create Notebook CR (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    K8S->>Webhook: Validate/Mutate Notebook (8443/TCP HTTPS mTLS)
    Webhook-->>K8S: Validated/Mutated CR
    K8S-->>User: 201 Created

    K8S->>ODH: Watch event: Notebook created
    ODH->>DSPA: Get pipeline config (8888/TCP HTTP)
    DSPA-->>ODH: Pipeline API endpoint + credentials

    ODH->>K8S: Create OAuth Client (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    ODH->>K8S: Create Route/HTTPRoute (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    ODH->>K8S: Create NetworkPolicy (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    ODH->>K8S: Create ServiceAccount + RBAC (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)

    K8S->>NB_Ctrl: Watch event: Notebook created
    NB_Ctrl->>K8S: Create StatefulSet (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    NB_Ctrl->>K8S: Create Service (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    K8S->>Pod: Start notebook pod
    Pod-->>NB_Ctrl: Pod ready

    Note over Culler,Pod: Flow 2: Idle Notebook Culling
    Culler->>Pod: Check /metrics for activity (HTTP)
    Pod-->>Culler: Last activity timestamp
    Culler->>Culler: Calculate idle time
    alt Notebook is idle
        Culler->>K8S: Stop notebook (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
        K8S->>Pod: Terminate pod
    end

    Note over User,Pod: Flow 3: User Access to Notebook
    User->>Router: Access notebook URL (443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    Router->>OAuth: OAuth Proxy - Check auth (80/TCP HTTP)
    OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OAuth token (443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    OAuth-->>Router: Authorized
    Router->>Pod: Forward request (notebook-port HTTP)
    Pod-->>Router: Notebook UI response
    Router-->>User: 200 OK notebook interface
